jsp tag 
jsp and servlet



1. Expression tag 
enclosed between <%= and %> 
is short for out.println() 
ex: 
<%= new java.util.Date() %> 
--> Tue Jul 27 11:42:40 CST 2010 

2. Directive tag 
enclosed between <%@ and %> 
ex: 
<%@ page language="java" %> 
ex: 
<%@ page import="java.util.*" %> 

3. Scriptlet tag 
execute a java source code 
ex: 
<% out.println("Hello World"); %> 

4. Declaration tag 
declare varaible or method 
ex: 
<%! int count = 0; %> 
count will become instance variable of the class 

5. use jsp in javscript
ex:
var isSetLater = '<%= request.getParameter("isSetLater") %>';
